article.headline: E. Washington 79, N. Colorado 76
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Parker Kelly nailed a 3-pointer with 14 seconds remaining to propel Eastern Washington to a 79-76 win over Northern Colorado on Wednesday night. Trailing 76-75, Parker's 3-pointer was assisted by Cliff Colimon as Eastern Washington (12-14, 6-7) overcame a 17-point deficit. Colimon led the Eagles with 22 points and nine assists. Northern Colorado (8-17, 5-9) stretched its lead to 50-33 with 17:21 remaining before Eastern Washington began to chip away. Parker hit a 3-pointer with 4:30 left to cap a 9-2 run, shaving the Bears' lead to 69-68. The Eagles captured a 74-72 lead on another Parker 3 with 1:50 left before surrendering their lead a final time on two free throws by Mike Proctor with 25 seconds remaining to trail 76-75. Kelly finished with nine points while Collin Chiverton contributed 19 points for Eastern Washington. Connor Osborne led with 17 points and Tate Unruh added 16 for Northern Colorado.
